	<key>readme</key>
	<string>## Usage

1. Copy multiline text (or select text and use the Hotkey).
2. Type the keyword (default `m2s`).
3. Choose a wrap/separator mode with ↑↓ and press ↩ to copy.

Blank lines are skipped. Quote characters inside wrapped lines are escaped.

## Workflow’s Configuration

* **Keyword** — Alfred keyword (default `m2s`)
* **Custom modes** — one mode per line: `WRAPPER||SEPARATOR||optional title`
  * Leave WRAPPER empty for no quotes
  * Escapes: `\s` space, `\t` tab, `\\` backslash
  * Reorder lines to change list order
* **UI language** — English or Chinese labels

## Hotkey

Bind the Hotkey object to convert the current macOS selection.

Forum: https://www.alfredforum.com/topic/23902-multiline-to-single-join-lines-with-quotes-separators/
Homepage: https://github.com/revolyw/alfred-multiline-to-single
License: MIT
</string>
